<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Degeneration, mitral valve, left, replacement</div><div><span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;">Section shows valvular tissue with myxoid degeneration.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Empyema</title>
    <created>20161222T235047Z</created>
    <updated>20260209T073745Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Empyema</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section taken from the pleura shows soft tissues with extensive necrosis, fibrin clots and infiltration of mixed inflammatory cells.</div><div>No granuloma nor evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170215T083003Z</created>
    <updated>20170215T083100Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;">Fibrosis with dystrophic calcification, aortic valve, replacement 2015032646</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman', times, serif;">Section of the aortic valve shows degenerative changes with fibrosis and dystrophic calcification. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br/></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>granulomatous inflammation, consistent with sarcoidosis.</title>
    <created>20210105T051233Z</created>
    <updated>20210105T080230Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>granulomatous inflammation, consistent with sarcoidosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show nodal tissue revealing small</div><div>aggregate of noncaseating epithelioid granulomas with</div><div>tightly packed epithelioid cells, admixed with</div><div>occasional Langhans giant cells and lymphocytes.</div><div>No mycobacterial microorganisms are identified by acid fast</div><div>stain. No fungus is identified by PAS.</div><div>The features are consistent with sarcoidosis.</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lung adenocarcinoma 分子報告</title>
