  <note>
    <title>Lung_ Bullae</title>
    <created>20170630T012426Z</created>
    <updated>20230825T081423Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Lung, ___ lobe, VATS wedge resection --- Bullae.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is composed of one piece of lung tissue</div><div>measuring _cm and _ gm. Bullae measuring up to _</div><div>cm are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The sections show bullae with fibrotic wall and chronic</div><div>inflammatory reaction. Mesothelial cell hyperplasia is</div><div>focally seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Metastatic adenocarcinoma, consistent with colorectal origin.  [Lung]</title>
    <created>20251009T060140Z</created>
    <updated>20251009T060254Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Lung, left upper lobe, VATS wedge resection --- </div><div>Metastatic adenocarcinoma, consistent with colorectal origin. </div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a piece of lung tissue measuring</div><div>_ x _ x _ cm and weighing _ g. </div><div>On cut section, a tumor measuring _ x _ x _ cm is seen</div><div>It is located _ cm to stapled margin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in 3 cassettes. </div><div>A1: Tumor</div><div>A2: Non-tumor</div><div>A3: Margin</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Section shows lung tissue infiltrated by complex tubuloglandular structures lined by neoplastic columnar cells with necrosis. </div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for CDX-2, consistent with metastatic adenocarcinoma of colorectal origin.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>metastatic adenocarcinoma, consistent with pulmonary origin</title>
    <created>20221209T051915Z</created>
    <updated>20250530T020801Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>metastatic adenocarcinoma, consistent with pulmonary origin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show bone tissue infiltrated by clusters of tumor cells bearing pleomorphic nuclei with eosinophilic cytoplasm. By immunohistochemistry, the tumor cells are positive for TTF-1 and AE1/AE3 but not GATA3, consistent with metastatic carcinoma of pulmonary origin.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>MIA, lung</title>
    <created>20231120T071437Z</created>
    <updated>20251021T074429Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Minimally invasive adenocarcinoma, nonmucinous (pT1mi).</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Specimen: Wedge resection of _ lobe, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and weighing _ g, fixed in formalin.</div><div>Tumor location: _ lobe</div><div>Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm</div><div>Tumor site: Periphery </div><div>Configuration of the tumor: Ill-delineated</div><div>Distance from surgical margin: _ cm</div><div>Visceral pleura: Free / Free but close to tumor</div><div>Non-neoplastic lung: Brown and spongy</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>A1: Tumor</div><div>A2: Non-tumor</div><div>A3: Surgical margin</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION: </div><div>Tumor type: Minimally invasive adenocarcinoma, nonmucinous</div><div>[lepidic: 90%; acinar: 10%]</div><div>Tumor grade: Grade I</div><div>Tumor size: </div><div>  Total Tumor Size Inclusive of Invasive and Lepidic </div><div>    Components: 9 mm in greatest diameter, measured on </div><div>    histological slides</div><div>  Invasive Tumor Size: &lt;1 mm in greatest diameter</div><div>(The invasive size is estimated by multiplying the percentage that is invasive by the total tumor size)</div><div>Extent of tumor:</div><div>  Pleural status: PL0</div><div>  Spread Through Air Spaces (STAS): Not identified</div><div>[pT1mi: Minimally invasive adenocarcinoma: adenocarcinoma (less than or equal to 3 cm in greatest</div><div>dimension) with a predominantly lepidic pattern and less than or equal to 5 mm invasion in greatest dimension]</div><div>Angiolymphatic invasion status: Absent</div><div>Perineural invasion status: Absent</div><div>Surgical margin:</div><div>  Parenchymal Margin: Free, 1.3 cm in distance</div><div>Treatment Effect: No known presurgical therapy</div><div>Lymph nodes: Not assessed </div><div>pTNM: pT1mi (AJCC cancer staging system, 9th edition)</div><div>TNM descriptors: Not applicable.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190701T015003Z</created>
    <updated>20260317T031203Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.google.com/search?q=meningothelial-like+nodules.&amp;rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;oq=meningothelial-like+nodules.&amp;aqs=chrome.0.69i59j0l6.488j0j7&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Minute meningothelial-like nodules.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lung tissue with an interstitial proliferation of cytologically bland oval to blunted spindle cells. Immunohistochemical analysis is performed, and these cells are positive for PR but not AE1/AE3, synaptophysin, chromogranin A or HMB45.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20211019T055321Z</created>
    <updated>20230706T043543Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Mucoid impaction of bronchi (MIB).<br/><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show extensive mucous plugging of the airways accompanied by air-way dilatation.</div><div>The mucus has laminated appearance with eosinophlic debris and Charcot-Leyden crystals (allergic mucin)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>NSCC adenosquamous</title>
    <created>20180510T044724Z</created>
    <updated>20240620T022413Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Non-small cell carcinoma</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lung tissue infiltrated by tumor cells in solid nests, individual cells and tubuloglandular structure.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells in tubuloglandular stucture are positive for TTF-1 and CK7; while the ones in</div><div>solid nests or as individual cells are positive for p40 and CK7. Staining for calretinin is negative.</div><div><br/></div><div>COMMENT: This is a non-small cell carcinoma with immunohistochemical stains favor separate adenocarcinoma and squamous components, which indicate the possibility of adenosquamous carcinoma, although this diagnosis can only be made based on a resection specimen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>NSCC NOS</title>
    <created>20191001T063144Z</created>
    <updated>20240620T022425Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Non-small cell carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows tumor cells in solid nests featuring necrosis,</div><div>marked cellular atypism and prominent nucleoli in a</div><div>lymphoid backgound. </div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for</div><div>AE1/AE3 but not p40, TTF-1, synaptophysin, chromogranin A,</div><div>PAX8, CD5 or CD117. Calretinin and WT-1 are negative,</div><div>excluding mesothelioma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Taken together, this is a non-small cell carcinoma, not</div><div>otherwise specified, with no clear squamous, adenocarcinoma</div><div>or neuroendocrine morphology or staining pattern.</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>NSCC, favor adenocarcinoma.</title>
    <created>20210322T101922Z</created>
    <updated>20251028T092134Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Non-small cell carcinoma, favor adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lung tissue infiltrated by tumor cells in solid nests, and individual cells. These tumor cells show enlarged and pleomorphic nuclei with prominent nucleoli and eosinophilic cytoplasm. Brisk mitotic activity is seen.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for TTF-1 and negative for p40.</div><div><br/></div><div>This is a non-small cell carcinoma with immunohistochemical stains favor adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div><b><span style="color:rgb(24, 133, 226);">註: </span></b>PDCA with a solid pattern:</div><ul><li><div>TTF1 and/or mucin+/ p40 - </div></li><li><div>TTF1 and p40 -/ mucin + </div></li><li><div>features of adenocarcinoma on cytology specimens, even if the biopsy shows a solid NSCC that is negative for TTF1, p40, and mucin stains. </div></li></ul></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>NSCC, favor SQCC</title>
    <created>20190211T023323Z</created>
    <updated>20230822T070723Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>non-small cell carcinoma, favor squamous cell carcinoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows infiltrative nests of tumor cells bearing large, vesicular nuclei with distinct nucleoli</div><div>and lightly eosinophilic cytoplasm. Some intermingled lymphocytes are seen. Lymphoid infiltrate is also seen in</div><div>adjacent tissue. </div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are strongly positive for p40 and CK5/6 but not TTF-1, or synaptophysin. Staining</div><div>for mucincarmine is negative. Weak intensity of nuclear staining of EBER is seen in some tumor cells.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:#EB0073;">Morphological squamous cell patterns are not present, but supported by stains.</span></div><hr/><div style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:10px;"><b><span style="color:rgb(24, 133, 226);">註:</span></b><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);"> In poorly differentiated carcinomas with a solid pattern, if the tumour is p40-positive but TTF1-negative, </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Organizing pneumonia</title>
    <created>20161208T082946Z</created>
    <updated>20250923T063803Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Organizing pneumonia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows benign lung tissue exhibiting fibroblastic plugs filling air spaces. No</div><div>evidence of granuloma or malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Penumatocele</title>
    <created>20160805T010104Z</created>
    <updated>20211026T082215Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show several thin-walled cysts with rupture. Focal fresh hemorrhage and dilated vessels are noted in lung parenchyma. Some neutrophils are seen in the bronchial space.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pleural nodules; anthracosis; hyalin</title>
    <created>20211117T083555Z</created>
    <updated>20230706T043543Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The pleural nodules show anthracotic</div><div>  pigment in a background of hyaline collagenized tissue.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pneumoconiosis</title>
    <created>20170424T002410Z</created>
    <updated>20170627T092004Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows lung tissue exhibiting numerous hypocellular, hyalinized collagenous nodules surrouded by histiocytes and lymphocytes in lung parenchyma and subpleural</div><div>region. Some spicules are present under polarized light. The histomorphology is   </div><div>consistent with pneumoconiosis. No micro-organism is identified by PAS, GMS,</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>primary pulmonary enteric-type adenocarcinoma r/o metastasis first</title>
    <created>20230717T063713Z</created>
    <updated>20230717T063755Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>adenocarcinoma.</div><div>see Comment.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lung tissue infiltrated by neoplastic columnar</div><div>cells with pleomorphic nuclei arranged in glandular pattern</div><div>and in small clusters.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for CK7,</div><div>CK20, CDX2 but not TTF-1, Napsin A, GATA3, and PAX8.</div><div><br/></div><div>Comment:</div><div>Metastases must be ruled out first, particularly from the</div><div>gastrointestinal system, before rendering a diagnosis of</div><div>primary pulmonary enteric-type adenocarcinoma</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pulmonary hamartoma</title>
    <created>20250506T024421Z</created>
    <updated>20250506T024458Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Pulmonary hamartoma </span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Microscopic description: </span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">The histologic sections reveal the presence of a well circumscribed benign pulmonary lesion composed of hyaline cartilage, fibroadipose tissue, smooth muscle and bland spindle cells set in fibromyxoid stroma. The mesenchymal elements appear to entrap benign respiratory epithelium. These findings support the above diagnosis.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SCC, primary or metastatic</title>
    <created>20180911T033804Z</created>
    <updated>20241209T091146Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Squamous cell carcinoma, primary or metastatic</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows tissue cores infiltrated by nests of</div><div>squamoid cells with cellular atypia and increased mitotic</div><div>activity in a desmoplastic stroma. Keratinization is focally</div><div>seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the tumor cells are positive for</div><div>p40 but not TTF-1. Some residual pneumocytes are highlighted</div><div>by TTF-1.</div><div><br/></div><div>The overall features suggest a squamous cell carcinoma,</div><div>either primary or metastatic, which cannot be differentiated</div><div>by morphology or immunohistochemical studies. </div><div>Clinico-radiological correlation is recommended.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Small cell carcinoma [SmCC]</title>
    <created>20170119T073947Z</created>
    <updated>20250512T065644Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Small cell carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows sheets and nests of neoplastic cells revealing medium sized cells with focal tumor necrosis and crush artifact. The tumor cells show finely granular chromatin, inconspicuous nucleoli and scant cytoplasm. Nuclear molding is also seen. </div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for AE1/AE3, synaptophysin but not chromogranin A or p40.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thoracis</title>
    <created>20140701T021310Z</created>
    <updated>20180213T042237Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br/></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">Adenocarcinoma with lepidic pattern</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div>Section shows lung tissue cores revealing adenocarcinoma with lepidic pattern, lined</div><div>by atypical pneumocytes with mildly enlarged and hyperchromatic nuclei.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the atypical pneumocytes are highlighted by TTF-1. Staining for</div><div>Ki-67 shows no significant increase in proliferation index.</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>Comment: An invasive component cannot be excluded in this limited specimen.</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> </span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The lung tissue shows fibrosis with fibrinopurulent exudates coating over the pleural side. The alveolar spaces are filled with fibrin deposition and proliferation of fibroblasts. Reactive hyperplasia of type II pneumocytes and interstitial fibrosis are also discerned. Emphysematous change is present. There is no evidence of malignancy.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><ul><li><br clear="none" /></li></ul><div style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><br/></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thymic cyst (thymus)</title>
    <created>20170103T004307Z</created>
    <updated>20170103T004326Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show a unilocular cyst lined by ciliated columnar cells. Adjacent thymic </div><div>tissue is seen. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TNM 須 clinical imaging correlation</title>
    <created>20180927T065149Z</created>
    <updated>20230706T043545Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>http://192.168.1.15/emr/EMR_TreeView.aspx</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Pathologic Stage Classification (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition)</div><div>Combining the previous report (S07-00539), it shows multifocal lung adenocarcinoma of different histopathologic types in bilateral lobes. Clinical-radiological correlation is mandatory for a proper staging.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
